overview: The user initiated a review of their sleep questionnaire application,
  providing a Statement of Work and a detailed questionnaire specification. The
  assistant performed a thorough analysis, identifying several gaps in the
  current implementation. A prioritized plan was then created, and the assistant
  began implementing the high-priority items. This included adding a 1-10
  severity scale for tiredness, complete with critical safety messaging for high
  scores. The assistant also implemented detection and reporting for Comorbid
  Insomnia and Sleep Apnea (COMISA) and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, integrating
  these into both the web and PDF reports. Finally, a new section with
  placeholder outbound links to various sleep and mental health resources was
  added to enhance the report's utility. The next step in the plan, implementing
  weighted EDS scoring, was about to begin.
